This is a classic data engineering challenge. The most difficult part of your request is the "Price" normalization, because a value like `1,234` is ambiguous: in the US, it's one thousand two hundred thirty-four; in Europe, it's one point two three four.

To handle this, I have implemented a **heuristic approach**: if a string contains both a dot and a comma, the script looks at which one comes last to determine the format. If it only contains one, it makes an educated guess based on the position of the separator.

You will need to install the `python-dateutil` library, as it is far more powerful than the built-in `datetime` for guessing messy date formats.

